  "doc_id": "15346",
  "text": "Registry data on THR due to #NOF were also analyzed with respect to AMD. To date, two studies have directly evaluated AMD and its association with hip fractures. One study found an 11% increase in the four-year odds of hip fracture only with geographic atrophy but not neovascular AMD, while the other study found a 9% increase in hip fracture with newly diagnosed AMD (AMD type was not well defined) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In the present study we also evaluated whether AMD was associated with #NOF, particularly as late AMD leads to vision loss and vision loss is known to increase the risk of falls and fractures [CITATION_3] .",
